OL,6,FThere is a slight variation between
OL,7,Fthe regions with 28% of children in
OL,8,FWales living in poverty, 24% in
OL,9,FScotland, and 22% in Northern Ireland.
OL,10,FThe rate is highest in England at 31%.
OL,12,FWales' children's commissioner meets
OL,13,Fchildren and families every week and
OL,14,Fshe says the stories they share are
OL,15,F"heartbreaking."
OL,17,FWith "poverty deepening" she says some
OL,18,Fpeople "don't have food to put in
OL,19,Ftheir lunchbox", and they "don't have
OL,20,Fenough money to buy new school shoes".
